1
00:00:08,599 --> 00:00:09,320
Who are you?

2
00:00:14,800 --> 00:00:16,039
Don't move and I'll spare your life.

3
00:00:16,960 --> 00:00:17,839
Let me ask you something.

4
00:00:18,320 --> 00:00:20,039
Where's the file on you and Su Zhuang?

5
00:00:21,120 --> 00:00:22,280
What file?

6
00:00:22,480 --> 00:00:24,199
I never saved any files.

7
00:00:24,800 --> 00:00:25,760
Who the hell are you?

8
00:00:27,199 --> 00:00:28,079
You want to die, is that it?

9
00:00:29,600 --> 00:00:30,280
Don't kill me!

10
00:00:30,920 --> 00:00:31,760
It's all on the computer.

11
00:00:31,879 --> 00:00:33,560
I'll give it to you, all of it.

12
00:01:13,120 --> 00:01:13,959
An attack.

13
00:01:15,359 --> 00:01:16,439
But in this room,

14
00:01:17,239 --> 00:01:18,920
there are no signs of a struggle.

15
00:01:19,040 --> 00:01:20,120
That actually explains

16
00:01:20,120 --> 00:01:21,599
why the room is so clean.

17
00:01:22,560 --> 00:01:23,439
You mean to say

18
00:01:23,439 --> 00:01:24,920
that after Shen Qing's incident,

19
00:01:25,200 --> 00:01:26,959
someone came back and deliberately cleaned up?

20
00:01:30,799 --> 00:01:32,319
Take a close look at this cabinet.

21
00:01:33,040 --> 00:01:34,159
Notice anything different?

22
00:01:39,040 --> 00:01:40,239
Something seems to be missing on the right.

23
00:01:41,879 --> 00:01:43,200
Judging by the gap and position,

24
00:01:43,200 --> 00:01:44,359
it should be another photo.

25
00:01:44,439 --> 00:01:46,799
And about the same size as the left one.

26
00:01:47,480 --> 00:01:48,680
If that's really the case,

27
00:01:49,239 --> 00:01:52,079
then that photo must hide a big secret.

28
00:01:52,640 --> 00:01:53,319
Also, Captain Li,

29
00:01:53,480 --> 00:01:54,000
take a look.

30
00:01:54,519 --> 00:01:55,680
In this photo of Shen Qing,

31
00:01:55,680 --> 00:01:57,159
the diamond necklace she's wearing

32
00:01:58,400 --> 00:01:59,599
must be worth a fortune.

33
00:02:09,080 --> 00:02:11,479
Was the necklace found anywhere else?

34
00:02:11,599 --> 00:02:12,280
No.

35
00:02:14,800 --> 00:02:17,360
Shen Qing wasn't wearing this necklace when she died.

36
00:02:17,599 --> 00:02:19,280
And it wasn't in her home either.

37
00:02:31,159 --> 00:02:32,400
Doesn't she have a study at home?

38
00:02:32,680 --> 00:02:33,919
There wasn't a dedicated study.

39
00:02:34,680 --> 00:02:35,919
No desktop computer was found?

40
00:02:36,199 --> 00:02:36,759
No.

41
00:02:37,439 --> 00:02:39,120
That means she used a laptop for work.

42
00:02:39,360 --> 00:02:41,199
Didn't you find a laptop in her home?

43
00:02:41,639 --> 00:02:42,639
None was found.

44
00:02:44,199 --> 00:02:45,879
Then it seems your deduction is correct.

45
00:02:46,280 --> 00:02:47,520
Someone really did break in last night.

46
00:02:48,479 --> 00:02:51,120
But why are there no signs of damage on the lock?

47
00:02:51,759 --> 00:02:52,759
Could it be someone she knew?

48
00:02:59,000 --> 00:02:59,919
Look at this spot.

49
00:03:00,319 --> 00:03:02,120
Doesn't it look like a place for a vase?

50
00:03:03,080 --> 00:03:03,639
Yes, it does.

51
00:03:22,159 --> 00:03:23,360
Sure enough, someone broke in.

52
00:03:41,840 --> 00:03:42,840
Don't try any tricks.

53
00:04:09,680 --> 00:04:10,520
Pipi, run!

54
00:05:42,879 --> 00:05:45,000
From the case report by the Economic Crimes Unit,

55
00:05:46,199 --> 00:05:46,800
this man

56
00:05:47,199 --> 00:05:48,560
is likely connected to Shen Qing's death.

57
00:05:48,920 --> 00:05:49,839
Wu Chengming.

58
00:05:50,839 --> 00:05:51,959
What's his background?

59
00:05:53,839 --> 00:05:55,439
Wu Chengming, fifty years old.

60
00:05:55,639 --> 00:05:56,879
Owner of Chengming Machinery.

61
00:05:57,680 --> 00:05:58,600
Recently,

62
00:05:58,759 --> 00:06:01,160
The Economic Crimes Unit had complaints of

63
00:06:01,639 --> 00:06:04,680
Chengming Machinery's debts and delays.

64
00:06:05,279 --> 00:06:06,800
And half a month ago,

65
00:06:06,800 --> 00:06:08,720
a crowd gathered to demand payment

66
00:06:08,920 --> 00:06:10,639
and clashed with factory security.

67
00:06:10,759 --> 00:06:11,920
Fortunately, no one was hurt.

68
00:06:13,199 --> 00:06:13,920
Anything else?

69
00:06:15,399 --> 00:06:17,920
The Economic Crimes Unit investigated him.

70
00:06:18,120 --> 00:06:19,160
They found Chengming Machinery's issues

71
00:06:19,160 --> 00:06:20,839
go beyond just unpaid bills.

72
00:06:22,519 --> 00:06:23,560
There are also major financial problems

73
00:06:23,560 --> 00:06:24,959
in how he's running the company.

74
00:06:25,319 --> 00:06:26,240
A month ago at Fengdu Bank,

75
00:06:26,399 --> 00:06:29,680
Chengming Machinery borrowed 55 million.

76
00:06:29,879 --> 00:06:32,000
The loan officer was Shen Qing.

77
00:06:33,120 --> 00:06:35,600
But the money wasn't used for production,

78
00:06:35,720 --> 00:06:36,839
nor to pay off suppliers,

79
00:06:36,959 --> 00:06:38,439
or to repay the bank.

80
00:06:38,959 --> 00:06:41,240
It mysteriously vanished from the account.

81
00:06:42,000 --> 00:06:43,360
Where is this Wu Chengming now?

82
00:06:43,560 --> 00:06:44,519
Since the case broke,

83
00:06:44,759 --> 00:06:46,480
the Economic Crimes Unit can't find him.

84
00:06:46,680 --> 00:06:48,079
It's like he vanished into thin air.

85
00:06:49,959 --> 00:06:51,279
Go to the Economic Crimes Unit right now

86
00:06:51,279 --> 00:06:52,240
and coordinate with them.

87
00:06:52,360 --> 00:06:53,720
We need to find Wu Chengming

88
00:06:53,720 --> 00:06:54,800
as quickly as possible.

89
00:06:55,240 --> 00:06:55,759
Yes, sir.

90
00:07:00,319 --> 00:07:02,279
How many times do I have to say it?

91
00:07:02,519 --> 00:07:04,319
I have no idea where that jerk ran off to.

92
00:07:04,519 --> 00:07:06,079
The three of us are about to starve.

93
00:07:06,480 --> 00:07:07,519
I can't find him either.

94
00:07:07,639 --> 00:07:09,399
I was hoping you cops could find him

95
00:07:09,639 --> 00:07:10,519
and ask him to his face

96
00:07:10,680 --> 00:07:11,720
if we're still married.

97
00:07:11,920 --> 00:07:12,879
If not, I'm filing for divorce.

98
00:07:13,040 --> 00:07:14,560
I'm done waiting on him!

99
00:07:23,360 --> 00:07:25,360
Yeah, the sooner the better.

100
00:07:25,680 --> 00:07:27,800
He's probably off under her spell,

101
00:07:28,399 --> 00:07:29,879
while you're at home crying alone.

102
00:07:30,040 --> 00:07:30,879
How miserable is that?

103
00:07:31,879 --> 00:07:33,600
What did you say? Under her spell?

104
00:07:34,160 --> 00:07:35,439
Cops better not be making things up.

105
00:07:35,639 --> 00:07:36,839
According to our investigation,

106
00:07:36,959 --> 00:07:38,920
Wu Chengming recently transferred

107
00:07:39,040 --> 00:07:40,560
a huge sum into a woman's account.

108
00:07:40,959 --> 00:07:43,639
And that woman, young and pretty,

109
00:07:44,319 --> 00:07:46,199
oh, those cherry lips,

110
00:07:46,199 --> 00:07:47,439
those delicate arched brows...

111
00:07:47,879 --> 00:07:49,480
One word: bewitching.

112
00:07:49,600 --> 00:07:50,959
Stop it, shut up!

113
00:07:51,319 --> 00:07:52,000
You're lying!

114
00:07:52,319 --> 00:07:53,439
Am I, though?

115
00:07:53,639 --> 00:07:55,199
How many times have you seen him lately?

116
00:07:55,360 --> 00:07:56,639
How many times have you called him?

117
00:07:57,360 --> 00:07:58,839
And every time you called,

118
00:07:58,839 --> 00:08:00,560
didn't he hang up in a hurry?

119
00:08:00,839 --> 00:08:01,800
Let me tell you,

120
00:08:02,079 --> 00:08:03,920
he's fallen into her honey trap.

121
00:08:04,120 --> 00:08:05,199
He's drowning in her embrace.

122
00:08:05,199 --> 00:08:06,480
He's lost in pleasure.

123
00:08:06,680 --> 00:08:07,399
Let me tell you,

124
00:08:07,600 --> 00:08:09,120
that woman has a stunning figure,

125
00:08:09,120 --> 00:08:10,959
all those gorgeous curves.

126
00:08:11,759 --> 00:08:12,399
Oh, really now!

127
00:08:12,399 --> 00:08:13,839
Wu Chengming, you Bastard!

128
00:08:14,240 --> 00:08:15,759
Didn't you say you liked my type?

129
00:08:15,959 --> 00:08:17,560
I'll tear that vixen apart!

130
00:08:17,560 --> 00:08:18,600
Enough, Song Xiulian.

131
00:08:18,920 --> 00:08:20,879
You're harboring a criminal.

132
00:08:21,120 --> 00:08:21,720
If you don't talk,

133
00:08:21,920 --> 00:08:23,439
we'll have to take you in for questioning.

134
00:08:24,360 --> 00:08:25,759
One last chance.

135
00:08:25,759 --> 00:08:26,800
Where is Wu Chengming hiding?

136
00:08:31,000 --> 00:08:32,120
He should be at...

137
00:08:33,200 --> 00:08:34,200
Liyuan Resort.

138
00:08:35,960 --> 00:08:37,480
He's got a long-term suite there,

139
00:08:38,440 --> 00:08:40,039
booked under someone else's name.

140
00:08:50,279 --> 00:08:51,240
Hey, I gotta say,

141
00:08:51,240 --> 00:08:52,720
your performance back there was amazing.

142
00:08:52,759 --> 00:08:54,039
You should be an actor.

143
00:08:54,600 --> 00:08:56,600
Enough, don't steal their jobs.

144
00:08:56,720 --> 00:08:58,279
Any more and I'd be Best Actor.

145
00:08:59,679 --> 00:09:00,879
Did you feel my charm?

146
00:09:04,240 --> 00:09:05,120
I need to be serious.

147
00:09:05,559 --> 00:09:07,200
If Boss were here, he'd scold me again.

148
00:09:07,279 --> 00:09:08,200
Tell me about the case.

149
00:09:08,440 --> 00:09:09,559
A loan this large,

150
00:09:09,799 --> 00:09:12,039
Shen Qing couldn't have approved it alone.

151
00:09:12,200 --> 00:09:14,480
Just as we were about to investigate her,

152
00:09:14,600 --> 00:09:15,879
she fell to her death.

153
00:09:16,240 --> 00:09:17,720
I think behind this case,

154
00:09:17,879 --> 00:09:19,639
there must be a hidden secret.

155
00:09:20,279 --> 00:09:21,240
You're right.

156
00:09:21,799 --> 00:09:23,720
We've stumbled onto a big one this time.

157
00:09:26,120 --> 00:09:26,759
Hey.

158
00:09:27,399 --> 00:09:29,919
Is this where Wu Chengming's wife meant?

159
00:09:30,399 --> 00:09:32,440
Yeah, this is it.

160
00:09:38,240 --> 00:09:39,360
Look, isn't that him?

161
00:09:40,639 --> 00:09:42,279
Hey, it really is Wu Chengming.

162
00:09:42,279 --> 00:09:43,600
Quick, hide, hide, hide!

163
00:10:02,600 --> 00:10:05,039
This old fox is leading us in circles.

164
00:10:05,960 --> 00:10:07,879
It's fine. I'll keep some distance.

165
00:10:08,679 --> 00:10:10,279
This Wu Chengming is a real piece of work.

166
00:10:10,600 --> 00:10:11,799
Ignoring his two kids at home.

167
00:10:11,799 --> 00:10:12,960
Out there finding a mistress.

168
00:10:14,320 --> 00:10:15,399
Just proves the old saying right.

169
00:10:15,919 --> 00:10:17,240
Men go bad once they get rich.

170
00:10:17,919 --> 00:10:19,240
Good thing you're broke.

171
00:10:19,879 --> 00:10:21,080
Hey, what kind of thing is that to say?

172
00:10:21,080 --> 00:10:22,720
Even if I had money, I wouldn't go bad.

173
00:10:22,919 --> 00:10:23,799
You know why?

174
00:10:24,759 --> 00:10:26,039
I don't want romance.

175
00:10:26,240 --> 00:10:28,080
I just want money to spend.

176
00:10:28,679 --> 00:10:29,759
You're shameless.

177
00:10:32,960 --> 00:10:33,919
He's pulling into the parking lot.

178
00:10:34,480 --> 00:10:34,960
Let's go.

179
00:10:39,480 --> 00:10:42,919
The old fox detoured to this hotel.

180
00:10:43,440 --> 00:10:45,320
I bet he's got another hideout here too.

181
00:10:45,639 --> 00:10:46,440
So what now?

182
00:10:46,440 --> 00:10:47,559
Let's nab him right here.

183
00:10:48,080 --> 00:10:48,679
Just the two of us?

184
00:10:49,200 --> 00:10:49,759
Yeah.

185
00:10:49,879 --> 00:10:51,360
Maybe we should wait for backup.

186
00:10:51,720 --> 00:10:53,360
He'll be gone before backup arrives.

187
00:10:53,600 --> 00:10:54,080
Good point.

188
00:10:54,080 --> 00:10:54,759
Go, go.

189
00:11:00,200 --> 00:11:01,879
Hey, I left my phone in the car.

190
00:11:02,759 --> 00:11:04,519
Oh no, this is bad. Run, run, run!

191
00:11:10,200 --> 00:11:11,840
Hey, my car! What are you doing?

192
00:11:12,039 --> 00:11:12,639
Ah!

193
00:11:16,799 --> 00:11:18,320
We really underestimated that old fox.

194
00:11:19,519 --> 00:11:20,720
I let my guard down.

195
00:11:25,720 --> 00:11:26,360
What's with you?

196
00:11:26,360 --> 00:11:27,279
Looking dejected.

197
00:11:28,879 --> 00:11:30,919
Boss, just discipline me.

198
00:11:31,399 --> 00:11:32,440
You didn't find Wu Chengming?

199
00:11:32,840 --> 00:11:34,000
I found him.

200
00:11:34,919 --> 00:11:36,200
But I let him slip away again.

201
00:11:36,919 --> 00:11:37,799
Tell me as we walk.

202
00:11:42,279 --> 00:11:43,320
With you spooking him like that,

203
00:11:43,600 --> 00:11:45,600
Wu Chengming might very well flee Fengdu.

204
00:11:45,799 --> 00:11:47,279
Catching him will be much harder now.

205
00:11:49,360 --> 00:11:50,879
That's why I'm asking to be disciplined.

206
00:11:51,080 --> 00:11:53,120
Will punishing you make him surrender?

207
00:11:57,200 --> 00:11:57,879
Boss.

208
00:11:58,840 --> 00:12:00,759
Can I still work on the case?

209
00:12:02,000 --> 00:12:03,639
You want to get paid to do nothing?

210
00:12:06,080 --> 00:12:06,759
Yes, Boss.

211
00:12:06,759 --> 00:12:08,080
I promise I'll get the job done.

212
00:12:08,080 --> 00:12:10,240
Enough. This is the forensics lab.

213
00:12:10,639 --> 00:12:11,399
You want to take an oath?

214
00:12:11,399 --> 00:12:13,039
Go do it under the flag in the courtyard.

215
00:12:13,519 --> 00:12:15,399
Sister Fei is always so Authoritative.

216
00:12:19,000 --> 00:12:20,000
Authentic dark chocolate.

217
00:12:21,639 --> 00:12:22,679
Not bad.

218
00:12:23,440 --> 00:12:25,480
Look at her, only here a few days.

219
00:12:25,480 --> 00:12:26,440
So considerate.

220
00:12:26,879 --> 00:12:27,840
Unlike some people.

221
00:12:27,840 --> 00:12:29,440
They only ever nag me for reports.

222
00:12:29,440 --> 00:12:30,720
Relentless calls.

223
00:12:33,120 --> 00:12:34,679
Look at how awful you look.

224
00:12:35,320 --> 00:12:36,240
You're so worn out you've turned gray.

225
00:12:36,240 --> 00:12:37,799
Go back to your office and rest a bit.

226
00:12:38,039 --> 00:12:40,320
I'll send the report once it's ready.

227
00:12:40,759 --> 00:12:42,000
My principle is,

228
00:12:42,000 --> 00:12:43,919
whenever I can talk face-to-face,

229
00:12:44,080 --> 00:12:45,720
I never read it in writing.

230
00:12:45,879 --> 00:12:47,639
I've heard it a million times.

231
00:12:48,080 --> 00:12:49,919
What's on paper isn't always reliable.

232
00:12:51,039 --> 00:12:53,159
I'd miss chances to catch the details.

233
00:12:54,039 --> 00:12:55,279
You always have an excuse.

234
00:12:55,679 --> 00:12:58,000
Just transfer here and examine with me.

235
00:12:58,440 --> 00:13:00,000
Notice how every time I show up,

236
00:13:00,000 --> 00:13:02,039
your examination goes incredibly smoothly?

237
00:13:02,639 --> 00:13:03,559
Deputy Captain Li.

238
00:13:04,159 --> 00:13:05,679
This overwhelming confidence of yours,

239
00:13:05,679 --> 00:13:07,120
when exactly did it possess you?

240
00:13:10,919 --> 00:13:12,519
Every time I face a homicide,

241
00:13:13,039 --> 00:13:14,200
I have no confidence at all.

242
00:13:15,720 --> 00:13:16,799
I'm terrified of making a mistake.

243
00:13:18,120 --> 00:13:19,399
of failing the dead,

244
00:13:20,240 --> 00:13:21,480
and letting down the living.

245
00:13:22,120 --> 00:13:24,559
The victim shows signs of a fatal fall.

246
00:13:24,919 --> 00:13:26,960
There's no sign of prior sexual assault.

247
00:13:27,919 --> 00:13:29,759
Other than the fatal fall injuries,

248
00:13:29,879 --> 00:13:31,120
there are no other external injuries.

249
00:13:31,840 --> 00:13:34,159
And no foreign traces were found on her.

250
00:13:35,799 --> 00:13:36,519
What about the tests?

251
00:13:36,519 --> 00:13:37,720
Toxicology tests were done.

252
00:13:37,720 --> 00:13:39,240
No signs of poisoning were found.

253
00:13:39,679 --> 00:13:40,399
What about this?

254
00:13:40,720 --> 00:13:42,120
The can left at the scene

255
00:13:42,240 --> 00:13:43,840
has also been thoroughly examined.

256
00:13:44,679 --> 00:13:46,039
The liquid residue inside the can

257
00:13:46,039 --> 00:13:47,240
is definitely beer.

258
00:13:47,480 --> 00:13:48,240
In conclusion,

259
00:13:48,240 --> 00:13:49,840
all the examinations we've conducted

260
00:13:49,960 --> 00:13:51,679
show no clear signs of a homicide.

261
00:13:52,159 --> 00:13:53,399
It's definitely a homicide.

262
00:13:59,279 --> 00:14:00,519
Before Shen Qing fell,

263
00:14:00,879 --> 00:14:03,840
her back was likely to the edge.

264
00:14:04,960 --> 00:14:05,840
Otherwise,

265
00:14:07,039 --> 00:14:09,159
she wouldn't have landed the way she did.

266
00:14:10,399 --> 00:14:13,440
No traces of a second person were found.

267
00:14:13,960 --> 00:14:14,720
Beyond physical traces,

268
00:14:14,720 --> 00:14:16,440
didn't you uncover any other clues?

269
00:14:16,799 --> 00:14:17,279
Yes.

270
00:14:17,720 --> 00:14:18,440
The victim

271
00:14:18,440 --> 00:14:19,080
was pregnant.

272
00:14:19,639 --> 00:14:20,399
How do you know?

273
00:14:23,720 --> 00:14:25,240
The position of her hands,

274
00:14:26,279 --> 00:14:27,879
and her second-floor room.

275
00:14:29,279 --> 00:14:30,519
Didn't you once say

276
00:14:30,960 --> 00:14:33,879
cops shouldn't mix feelings into a case?

277
00:14:34,799 --> 00:14:37,440
That doesn't mean we have no feelings.

278
00:14:37,960 --> 00:14:38,759
Right, Boss?

279
00:14:39,480 --> 00:14:40,440
Jiang Han is right.

280
00:14:43,120 --> 00:14:44,519
Ever since Captain Zhao left,

281
00:14:45,600 --> 00:14:46,919
I've felt this even more deeply.

282
